604Please dispatch a tech as soon as possible to replace ink ribbon on register 1 as well as testing printer to ensure its able to print both sides of a check Please have technician follow the instructions below after he has changed the ink ribbon on register 1. You can perform a printing test by performing the following. Test Printing on Slip PaperMake sure all the covers are closed.While pressing the Release button, turn on the printer.After the Slip LED flashes, insert the slip paper. If there is no print on the paper, it is a hardware issue. Please troubleshoot the ink ribbon or the printer itself. If the test print works without issue, please determine if the printer attempts to print when endorsing a check. The printer is quite noisy when it tries to print, so it should be noticeable if it is trying. Please let us know if no attempt is being made, and contact helpdesk so we can gather the transaction details and retail error/CHM logs.

T1886BMH1103 - FAN REDUNDANCY IS LOST.|15QX144 | PLEASE PERFORM FULL SERVER REPLACEMENT | POWEREDGE R650XSCI Name: PowerEdge R650xsDescription - t1886bmh1103 - Fan redundancy is lost.|15QX144 | Please perform Full Server Replacement | PowerEdge R650xsAdditional Comments from Pomeroy:2025-05-14 09:41:57 - Target Integration Service Account (Additional comments)Tracking number: 1Z1F43650157125571Return tracking: 1Z1F43650357632902Part sent: 210-AZKL-STSerial number: 5JDX144---HQ DEPOT TO SHIP 210-AZKL-ST---File TSR20250514013657_15QX144.zip has been renamed by system---Vendor Technician tasks:1.Please don't touch any other server apart from the server to be replaced. Verify the service tag of the server to be replaced and start the activity.2.Remove/unplug the power cables and network cables from the old rack server. Remove hard disks from the hard disk bay on the front side of the server. MARK THEM SO YOU KNOW WHICH SLOT THEY CAME FROM.3.Open the old server and look for BOSS-S1 controller card along with 2 SSD disks (M2 form factor), remove it from the server. This needs to be moved to the new server.4.Remove all hard disks in the front side (3.5 T and 16 T) from OLD server and install them in the NEW server in the same slots. (need to swap all disks from old server to new server in the same slots).5.Install the BOSS-S1 controller card along with 2 SSD disks (M2 form factor) in the slot in the new server.6.Close the top panel of the server AND insert the server in the server slot and plug in power cables and network cables (in the same slots as before) and DONT POWER ON THE SERVER.7.Have tech tell you if it starts to turn on (lights come on). If it does, turn off the server.8.DO NOT POWER ON THE SERVER UNTIL YOU VERIFY THE BOOT ORDER. (IF YOU TURN ON THE SERVER WITHOUT RESETTING THE BOOT ORDER, IT WILL WIPE THE EXISTING DRIVES).9.After the server replacement, ask the tech to write a note on the paper and place it in the old(bad) server. That paper should state Replace system board. That way, when vendor analyses the server, the techs at Washburn know to replace the system board before returning it back into the parts pool.10.Remind vendor L2 to update the ServiceNow CI with the new asset tag from the new server.
